content.detailedDescription: My boyfriend and i were driving toward our storage unit in south austin at around noon on sunday, april 1st, 2007. we both noticed a brilliantly shining silver object flying very slowly at low altitude at a perpendicular angle to our course. it looked as if it was producing it's own light. we could not make out the shape of the object due to the shear intensity of the light it produced. we watched it for about 2 minutes when it quite suddenly disappeared before our eyes. it did not move beyond our range of sight. it simply faded over a period of 2 seconds, and then disappeared completely.
content.summary: Bright silver light/craft disappeares before our eyes-- south austin

content.detailedDescription:
I was sitting on my porch at 21:42 lighting a cigarette, looking towards the north west, observing the stars in the exceptionally clear sky.  a moving object, appearing star like, caught my attention just above the western horizon, tracking eastward in a straight line.  the object was in the sky at about a 45 degree angle.  the object appeared much brighter than any stars in the sky, and had just a hint of orange to it.  as the object tracked through the sky to the point due north of my position, it started to fade in brightness, quickly disappearing all together as it hit a point north by north east in the sky.  this event lasted no more than 45 seconds.
i had thought at first the object may have been an airplane.  due to the fact that there were no flashing marker lights which should have been clearly visible considering the brightness of the object, and there was absolutely no sound of engines either jet or propeller, i dismissed the notion of an airplane.
secondly i thought of the object as a satellite, but due to the exceptional brightness and lack of clouds for it to disappear behind, i also dismissed that idea.
finally, i had considered a shooting star, and also dismissed that idea since there was no trail produced by the object.
it was not until the object rapidly faded and ultimately disappeared from sight that i began to consider the idea of a ufo.  given my quiet country location, and having 3 airports and an airforce base all within 100 miles, i have the opportunity to see and hear many objects passing through the skies during the day and at night.
the utter silence i think is what ultimately brought me to the decision to file a report.  never before on such a quiet, windless, and clear night have i seen something of this nature.
content.summary: Object passing west to east through clear sky

content.detailedDescription: Me and a friend were traveling east by car on 143rd street around 84th ave. when suddenly i saw something move across the night sky.  before i could even open my mouth to tell my friend about it he said, "oh my god, did you see that?"  it was a very clear night, my car said it was 41 degrees f, and we could even see some stars (very rare for orland park).  what we both saw was like a shooting-star but what made it completely different was it's speed and color.  it was an aqua-marine/teal color and when it went across the sky it didn't leave a trail, like a shooting star does.  it traveled across a huge amount of sky  in a pretty straight line in less than a second, but it was bright enough for both of us to see it.  after a second it just disapeared in the sky.  my first thoughts were extraterrestral because i am unaware of anything man made that can cover such a large amount of sky in a second.  i am unhappy that it was such a short experiance because my friend and i might have been the only ones on the road who saw it, although i wasn't looking at the sky and it grabbed my attention easily. if anyone else saw this please let me know.
content.summary: An object that covered a large area of sky in less than a second

content.detailedDescription:
My wife and i were attending the annual fire works show at the local city park. after parking our car we got our lawn chairs out and were commenting to some other people near us what gorgeous weather it was for a fire works show. as i was looking up at the cloudless sky, i noticed a moving "star" that appeared to be the space lab. i commented that "the space lab must be moving directly over iowa at the time". then while trying to fix my wife's attention on the object, it stopped! i'm just smart enough to know that "stars" and space objects do not stop their forward motion and pointed it out to several other people within ear shot. i continued to watch it to see if it would continue to move but "stars" don't just start and stop and neither do orbiting space vehicles. i must admit that it was completely dark by this time and my gaze did wander to the remaining fire works show for no more than 5 minutes. with completion of the show my line of sight was directed back to the "star" that quit moving and within no more than 2 to 3 minutes, it suddenly moved ....But at a 90 degree angle to what it had been traveling when i first noticed it. originally, it had moved in an easterly direction prior to stopping but the second move was directly northbound. my wife and i spoke about it but she poo-pooed it as just my imagination but i know what i saw and to this day, i'm convinced i witnessed something out of the ordinary that evening. 

when the object did finally depart northbound (at a very high altitude)it moved out of my line of vision within 2 to 3 seconds. this thing really moved!
content.summary: It was a moving "star" or space lab but then quite suddenly stopped!

content.detailedDescription:
last night ( april 14th 2007) my boyfriend and i were driving from dubuque, iowa going to a relatives house in darlington, wisconsin i was on the passengers side of the car and my boyfriend was driving. we were ten minutes away from darlington when i saw an extremely bright light about 1 or 2 miles ahead of me on my right side. i had no idea what it was but i knew it wasn't a plane because it was way to bright and not moving that fast.

whatever it was was going in the opposite direction as we were. as the we drove closer to the light we were at an angle where we were looking at the bottom of some kind of triangular flying craft, there were three white lights, one in the front of the craft and two in the back, in between the two back light was a flashing red light. i'm assuming the rest of the craft was black because the sky was pitch dark and all i could see were the lights. 

when i was looking up at the craft i was scared and in shock, for some reason i wanted to hold my stomach, probably to protect my unborn child. i couldn't stop looking at it, but when i couldn't see the lights anymore i got really scared and told my boyfriend to speed up.

the craft didn't seem to move fast it was going about the same speed we were, when we were at the same point it was it was moving slowly kind of hoovering. i tried to take a picture with my cell phone but there wasn't enough light and the craft was to far away. i kept staring at it until i couldn't see the lights anymore.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Triangular craft with 3 white lights and a flashing red light

content.detailedDescription: It was about 9:15pm when i went outside, because i wanted to look at this star, which i think is a planet, to the west sky. so i was sitting in a chair    looking in the west sky because it was so clear that night, and i remember telling myself that it would be strange if i saw something tonight because there was little league baseball at the park which made me feel like no one would of even seen the stars due to the field lights!.  well about 10, 15 minutes go by and i tell myself to go inside but to the other way around my house that way on the way in i could see that star before i go inside. alright well a soon as i turn around i start walking around the other side of my house and with the corner of my right eye i see some red pulsing lights, threw my neighbors trees. and i tell myself what the heck , and across the street my other neighbor is pulling in her drive way , and i say i don't care im gonna look at this thing. well to get a better view i have to walk to my curb, i was looking the whole way and it was so slow , no sound , just 2 red pulsing lights at the same time , it was like floating north then it make like a quick jump and shifted  directly east and the lights weren't as clear anymore i thought my eyes were straining , then as it floated away east , threw each pulse the 2 lights were getting closer together  i took 3 pulse's  for the 2 lights to become 1 light. after i saw that happen it seemed like the object was far away but it didn't look like it, it was the lights fading  slower and slower to nothing! i ran inside to tell my brother and step dad because i know i had just seem something in the sky that is rare i saw it transform who knows. my eyes were teary i was so shocked and sure and straight serious. i went back out with my step dad's video cam. and stayed outside to try to get it on tape but it never came around. this was my sighting i hope u refer it. and thank you for hearing my sighting.
content.summary: I was walking back inside my house when 2 red pulsing lights caught my eye big lights and pretty far apart .

content.detailedDescription:
I was getting my car washed at the eldorado car wash in laguna niguel. i was standing outside scannning the sky (as i always do) looking for ufos'. when i saw a red baloon high up in the (as high as the low clouds maybe 1000ft) at first i thought i saw a ribbon dangling down from the balloon and said to myself "well that one is a balloon for sure i can even see the string on it" it was gently floating across the sky just like you would expect a balloon to do. then i took my eyes off it to see how my car was doing and when i looked back it was gone. i couldn't find it for a minute and then i saw it way far away from where it had been. and i began to get more interested in it because i didn't the wind could have blown it that far, and as i watched i notice it was no longer moveing it seemed to be stationary but slowly getting smaller. at that point i called my wife and told her i was watching a possible ufo. then it dissappeared behind a cloud. i had been standing away from most of the other people waiting for thier cars. i now moved closer to the crowd and leaned on a rail still scanning the sky which was partialy cloudy and i caught sight of it again directly over the car wash now and there was two of them. there was a woman in front of me reading a book and i said to her "excuse i would like someone else to witness that there is something strange up in the sky" and pointed out the two red balloons that were above the carwash (i still wasn't sure what they were so i was to embarrased to say "oh look ufos") and she looked up at them and went right back to book. then i remembered my cell phone camera and set it up to take pictures and when it was ready to go, they were gone, but my car was ready so i went back home. i got my camera and took my wifes car down to be washed (it took me about 40 minutes home and back) i didn't think it would still be there but it was and i got these photos and a short video.
if you zoom in on these pictures you can see an aura around the balloon.
content.summary: Looked like a red balloon

content.detailedDescription:
I honestly don't know what it was. around 1:30pm or 1:45om, i was outside of a pep boys in south austin (texas), in the parking lot, with my boyfriend. we were waiting for the tow truck guy to show up to tow our car back to our house. the sky was a bright, flat blue. not one single cloud in the sky. and i see this.... thing. this silver thing hanging in the sky. i laughed and poked my boyfriend in the arm, then pointed at it, saying "think it's a ufo?" we both laughed a little, but... the more we watched it, the more we couldn't dismiss the idea. we stopped laughing and watched it.

first of all, it was very high up in the sky. higher than you normally see birds for sure. and even if a bird was up that high, it wouldn't be anywhere near as large as the thing. definitely bigger than a balloon. i'd wager to say it was bigger than a car.

second, it was silver. it was obviously silver, and highly reflective. it kept kind of "twisting" in the air. as we watched this thing, we began describing it outloud, planning what i would report seeing. i said that the way it was flashing--brilliantly flashing--was like a coin flipping in the air. my boyfriend shouted "yes!" it kind of pulsed with reflected light, and my he remarked that it looked like it was doing it rhythmically, in a pattern. not erratic.

it was most certainly round in shape, no visible fins or wings... in fact, we were certain it wasn't an airplane, because shortly after we spotted it, a large white passenger plane flew near it. to me, from where i was standing beneath it, it appeared that the object was closer to the ground than the plane. and if so, and if it was a plane, shouldn't it have been clearly definable as such? the plane made a loud noise, but the object made no noise at all.

we watched this thing, transfixed, as it moved in a straight line against the wind, appearing to go west. then it paused. then continued to move west. i watched it until i could no longer see it anymore. at its furthest distance, when i could no longer see the object properly, i could still see the bright flashing.

i'm interested in seeing if anyone else in austin reports seeing what i saw.
content.summary: Metallic sphere hovered and flew over south austin in mid-day, flashing, no noise, no clouds, very visible.

content.detailedDescription:
I was leaving the back of central market westgate store moving a powerjack to the other dock when i heard a jet passing over head. being a plane lover i naturally looked up and watched a white fed x plane desending in its flightpath toward bergstrom international airport. as the plane passed through the sky it seemed to pass near a round, bright object. i focused my eyes on this object forgetting about the plane. the object was metallic, round or disc in shape and texture. the sky was a clear blue with very thin clouds at higher levels. the object seemed not to be moving when i first witnessed it then it began to move westward very slowly. 
 at this time my boss s.H. passes by me in the back lot as i am staring at the object and they ask me what i was doing. i responded that i was looking at the disc in the sky. they then proceeded to look for it but by now it had become small in the sky and not as bright. i pointed to it as best i could and they serched the sky till they saw it too. they discribed the same thing i had been watching now for at lest ten minutes. we stood and watched for another five minutes or so till it vanished from sight. there were no lights visible yet it was very bright and metallic. i could see the sunlight reflecting of the side. silverish and golden. there was also no sound that i could detect. after the object was gone i went back to work. -rene aguirre
content.summary: A silverish metallic disc in the western sky. moving westward then stopping.Then starting again.

content.detailedDescription:
I have had repeated close encounters with entities over the years. these normally took the form of obe's and did not include the typical grey alien beings. rather the beings took many forms, and always had an enormously powerful effect on my personal spiritual development. at no time did i ever equate these experiences with the ufo phenomena. 

however, during a 6 month period in 1992 my family and i were visited on numerous occasions in what appeared to be a fairly common fashion according to research i conducted following the events. at the time i was relentlessly forced into convinction that a foreign intelligence was determined to reach me and members of my family in what could only be described as a deeply spiritual message.

of the many incidents the one that sticks out the most began late one evening. my wife and two young children were asleep in their own rooms (daughter 4 and son 1). the night was eerily quite. i was experiencing feelings of being watched, chills, unwarranted fear, ringing in my ears and rapid heart beat. my two large dogs were also experiencing fear and distress. for no reason that i can explain i went around our home and turned on all the lights - going downstairs was particularly frightening. 

i then turned on the tv. in a matter of minutes the atmosphere became truly strange. first, every channel i turned to was featuring shows on ufo's! in an instant i was experiencing feelings of death, and judgement. suddenly i sensed/envisioned a being entering my son's room. at that very instant he began crying and calling out. the timing betwen those two events was chilling. as i went down the hallway and opened his bedroom door he was fast asleep and lying on his back. what caught my attention was for a split second i thought i saw a bright blue glowing ball of light on the centre of his forehead. at that very instant ths 1 1/2 year old sat up and waved out his bedroom window and then laid back down and was deep asleep. i picked him up and he was so deeply asleep that i could not wake him.

although the event was very strange, i felt that i was either imagining things, or, that there was nothing i could do other than remain awake and stand in vigil over my family. i went back to the living room. in seconds i saw/felt something go into my daughter's room. at once she began to scream. i ran down the hall and as i opened her bedroom door i felt something walk right through me. my head felt like it was standing straight up and i was shuddering - i'm experiencing mild chills as i write. as i stood in the doorway my daughter looked at me and screamed. somehow i 'knew' that whatever was in her dream and passed through me in the doorway and that she had mistaken me for whatever it was. by the time i got to her side she was also deeply asleep! i remember thinking that hollywood couldn't have produced a scarier film as this was becoming extremely strange and frightening. 

oddly, i felt very familiar with all of those sensations, although i couldn't place when exactly i had ever encountered anything like what was happening. on another level, something was begining to breakdown within me. in the past i had kept some very strange experiences at what could be described as an intellectual arm's length when it came to my sense of reality or world view. suddenly, these very same feelings were clearly happening outside of my imagination or so it seemed, as other people appeared to be experiencing being acted upon! 

in an effort to combat this encounter, i chose act as if nothing was happening and to go to bed myself. ordinarily it takes me quite a while to fall asleep, but on this night it seemed as if i had just laid my head down and i 'sank' deep into the pillow and was asleep in an instant. the next thing i knew i was standing in my hallway in my dream. as i have had many obe experiences i 'knew' i was dreaming and cold actually govern my actions much as if i were awake. i looked down the hall into the bathroom and was shocked to see and alien looking directly at me. i 'knew' the he had been who was in the house earlier and had somehow 'arranged' to get me to see him. he was approximately 5 feet tall, had grey skin and only one large black eye, his left. this was shaped similarly to the common version of the grey alien beings.

deeply afraid and shocked i woke up immediately. again, i sensed the being moving into my son's room, and again my son called out in his sleep. i was both shocked, afraid and somehow accepting of the situation. i got up and checked on my son again and he was asleep as before. i returned to bed, but rather than try to sleep, i turned on a light and began to read. there was no way i was going back to sleep! at that moment, i sensed the being coming into our bedroom and my wife jumped right out of a deep sleep and screamed! without wasting a second i asked her, "what were you dreaming about"? she replied that she was on an operating table and a number of aliens were there. one of them told her not to be afraid, he had 'only one eye, his left one'!         

she fell back asleep in what seemed like seconds. for the next few hours the being kept wandering through the house. i could sense where he was, and sure enough my family would talk or call out when he 'seemed' to be in their rooms. at dawn, i finally fell asleep myself. in the morning my daughter came out of her room and told me that she had seen a spaceship floating over our boat that was stored in the backyard. this 4 year old child went on to describe the ship (as above) and that there were2 being on our back deck and three in her room. they had inserted a long needle into her belly button that hurt terribly. she was concerned that she was going to bleed on her bed. i interupted the procedure and then they left.
she later indentfied the beings as the grey type with shiny black eyes and black one piece suits.

i can recount many more such experiences. what i feel i must do however is to undergo regressive hypnosis and remember what was been said to me as i am convinced that something very important was shown to me.

thank you for reading.

michael beighton

content.detailedDescription: It was end of dec. 1977 or 1st of jan 1978 i was on my snowmobile after taking my girl freind home. i was riding across lake oakland when i noticed some lights that seemed to be trailing me off to the side. i slowed down and noticed a green and red light that seem to flash intermintantly and every other time there was a yellow light that flashed to. i was going to stop when i noticed a bright blueish white light that seemed to be searching thru the houses and the woods. i came around a section of the lake and there it was 50 feet or less from me. i freaked out and tried to get home all i can remember is a bright light hit me and and it was like a suspended animation i was riding my snowmobile but not going anywhere. all i know is that when i got home it was after midnight and i dropped my girl off at 9 or 9:15 pm and it was less than a twenty min. ride home. this i cant explain. i dont even remember getting home. i know that i had a semi-circular shape mark on my leg with a bunch off little holes that looked exactly like those of the people on the history channel they are showing on friday night 4-13-07 (south america). the mark is still there puncture marks are hard to see though. after watching that ufo show i figured i should find what i could on the wed and see if anyone was interested in my story since this happened around the same time as what was happenning in s. america 1977. thanks.
content.summary: Green, red, yellow flashes. the same as in s. america 1977 on history channel

content.detailedDescription:
My son and i were returning home after an evening walk up to the mountain base.  it was very large, guessing the size of a cargo plane, the side view was shaped like a cigar with lights all around, moving very, very slowly, seeming to defy gravity.  it was very low, just along the cliff ridge, tree tops.  we losts sight of it as it grew darker and we could not see it at all after watching it for about 15 minutes, from up the hill as we walked down the hill to our home. it was just over the trees along mountainous ridges that line kam hwy., along kaneohe bay.  

when i first noticed it i just looked for a while, expecting it, at any moment, to become clear as to what it was, what was going on, but as we walked closer, i was thinking it was too large to be so low, going so slow, making no noise, i realized it was quite possibly a ufo. it was unlike anything we had ever seen or had knowledge of and my son (now a pilot), was into aircraft, yet didn't know of any us aircraft that looked like that. he thought it might be a military experiment since kaneohe marine corps base was nearby, sited on kaneohe bay (i have now learned it is a possibility because we have learned new technology from visiting ets since 1947).  either way, it was a ufo, either visiting ets or us government testing of flying saucers.

i felt very special, privileged to have been able to see such a sight in my lifetime, although i did not report it for, back then, to make such claims, people thought you a loon.  i received confirmation of our sighting a few days later when the local news reported numerous people on the other side of the island (leeward side) reported ufo sightings.   it had a great impact on me, causing me to think of it for days, weeks, years on end and, as a result, i believe ets have/are visiting earth.
content.summary: Cigar-shaped ufo with lights moving very slowly over small mountain ridge, tree line

content.detailedDescription: I was walking to the park on bristol and warner with my kids about 1:00 pm march 31st. i spotted an unusual object in the sky along side a cluster of spherical shaped objects over costa mesa. about a minute after, my oldest son spotted another object to the right of this thing. when we first saw the second object, it looked like a cigar or an unsharpened pencil. a short while later it seemed to morph into a balloon or a tadpole. once it morphed, it started to move like a ballon in the sky. 30 minutes later [while at the park], the firt object we saw began to release shperical objects that would move away from it, but would return in a matter of minutes. as the day went on, more objects began to appear. i decided to call a photographer friend of mine to help me take pictures of these object. i went to his house about 4:30pm. when i on my way there. i saw an object that totally blew my mind. it had the shape of an arrowhead and its color was a dirty brown. this particullar object, was so close, i saw a lot of detail. as it flew over my car, i heard nothing. it almost seemed like it was scanning the neighborhood it was flying over. i told my friend about it and we went directly to his back yard. what we saw at that time was a group of spheres forming basic shapes [a perfect triangle]. this happened through the day and probably after the sun went down.
content.summary: Circular ufo with a tail or a flying fish

content.detailedDescription: On march 20, 2007 around 3pm my friend (scott) came over to my house to visit. my roommate (charlie) and i greeted him out in the front yard and that's when we observed a bright ball of light moving around a thunderstorm. the thunderstorm was approaching us slowly from the north and we still had sunshine above us. the clouds were dark, so the ufo was easy to see. it seemed like it was less than half a mile away. the object did a number of movements. it darted left to right while it ascended/descended and vice versa. the most impressive maneuver was a series of figure eights. during that time charlie and i went inside to grab our cameras. charlie took 11 pictures of the object with his digital camera and i got a little over a minute of footage with my camcorder.  the ufo went nw out of our view. we only saw that one ball of light during that time, but when we reviewed the film, there was more than one object. the film somehow picked up more activity, very close to us, at least 50 yards away from the camcorder. the first object is a streak of something moving so fast it is hard to catch it on the pause button. it looks very similar to a rod. the second object is a ball of light that descends from the top of the screen all the way to the ground, and it seems to go into the ground. it was very close to me. i'm so surprised that my friends and i never knew that it was there. the 3rd and 4th objects seem to fly in formation off in the distance, and the 5th object is the one that did the figure 8's which got our attention to take pictures.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering

content.detailedDescription: My daughter was driving home shortly after dark from her boyfriends ranch in the bears paw mountains outside of havre, when she noticed an unusual light in the sky over a mountain top. she said the color was fire like orange and very bright. she pulled the truck up and watched it. it then split into two orange lights and one flew very quickly away to her right, and then very quickly back together and joined the one it had left. she said the head lights, and the dashboard lights went out, but she said the music on the cd player kept playing. she came home hysterical, shacking and crying. she said she'd never been so scared. i can tell you, i've been in the moutains, and rafting with this girl when we where stalked by a momma and two year old grizzly, and had one, flat run us out of our camp after dark after we had been rafting all day.I have never seen her so scared. she isn't the hysterical kind. i'm kind of a ufo buff after having many sightings in my life, but she always treats me like i'm weird. well, now this is her third sighting, but the only one so close up and while she was alone. she was scared!!!After she watched this thing do the split and rejoin, she said it just disapeared, this fact seem to frighten her more then seeing it. she said she felt like she was being stalked for the next 30 miles home.She knows enough from being around me, that she kept an eye on the clock the whole way home. she said she glanced at it every couple of minutes to make sure there was no missing time. boy, was she shook up.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change
content.summary: There was a bright orange light over a moutain top. it split into two and then rejoined itself and took off.

content.detailedDescription:
My wife and i were driving west on i90 from buffalo in seperate cars on april 3rd, 2007 when we spotted two ufo's.

we had just left my friends house and had only been driving about 15-20 min. when i noticed a strange looking, almost luminescent small cloud in the sky ahead of me. it was a clear night with a few puff ball clouds in the sky. almost as soon as i noticed the strange cloud a glowing orange-silver light dropped down from the left and made a reverse "j" into the cloud. it then turned into two lights.
 i watched it for about 30 seconds, before i decided to call my wife, whom i was following. just as i picked up the phone, she called me and i answered with,"do you see that?" she replied,"what is that?" we stayed on the phone watching these two lights that were absolulty still. we drove for about 6 min. at 70 mph until we passed them floating about 200-300 feet off the ground and maybe a quarter mile to our right just past the silver creek exit, maybe 2-3 miles past.
  the oval balls had a very unearthly glow that radiated from them. we were close enough, that if it was a plane or an ultralight, i could have told you the make and model. i am an airplane buff and an outdoorsman, and i can tell you that what we saw was not of this world. i always thought i would stop and stare at something like this, but it scared me so bad i'm shaking typing this.
content.summary: 2 ufo's spotted for 7 min by silver creek, ny

content.detailedDescription: On the night of april 10th at 10:30 pm i was standing outside in the back yard looking up at the sky when i noticed two objects coming from the south they were side by side and when they were over head the one on the right shifted to the left at a 90 degree angle increased speed then shifted back to the right at a 90 degree angle in front of the other craft it only took around 7 seconds for both craft to go from horizon to horizon and lost sight of it my first thought was this must be a top secret aircraft ufo never entered my mind i was fascinated by what i saw i have never seen anything perform like that i called my wife back in missouri and told her what i had just seen and that it was the wildest thing i had ever seen what really stood out was there was no noise maybe just the slightest sound of a light breeze and the way they performed any information you can give me would be greatly appreciated thank you for your time.
content.summary: Two objects moving at high rate performing incredible manuevers craft made no sound

content.detailedDescription:
Near the end of september 1999 i was living in the east end of thunder bay ontario. i had two sightings of the same craft during this week the adress was 601 mcleod apt. 3. it was late wednesday/early thursday. my tv was broken so i was sitting in the dark when i noticed a light through my curtain. i opened up my curtains to see a light. the light alternated colors. i'll secribe this to the best of my ability. at fiest it may have been blue then turned red and then green. when it changes colors it would let off short bolts of electricity of that paricular color. when it completed a cycle of colors it would go into a rapid pattern that resembled a child scribbling on a paper. that light would be pink. when it was done scribbling it would turn a dull light pink and fill the night sky with this color. it would literally blind me, and i would have to blink over and over until my sight returned.
 during the whole time it was drifting from left to right. it was moving slow. it seemed to be running some kind of test. it appeared to be over lake superior. i don't know what was over there for it be testing. 

i remember watching it with my cat. i stuck my cat in the window and the cat seemed not to like it....It just gave a fearful meow. 

i tried to take pictures but the camera batteries were dead. i watched it over and over for the next few hours.


a few nights later it came back. this time i saw it come in. it was about 2:30 in the morning. i was laying on the couch looking out the window as my tv was still out. around that time i saw a white light coming in. i thought that was a weird way for a plane to come in. then it just stopped. all i could think was they're back and they started doing the same thing. this time i felt fear as i was wondering what the hell do they want.
 this time i wanted to phone the airforce, but didn't want to end up in a room with someone telling me that i didn't see anything. i didn't have a phone and the payphone was down the street, but i figured if i tried that they would abduct me. i also thought i shoulds never tell anyone of this as they would believe that i was crazzy.
 i watched this time for maybe 3 hours before jets showed up, and started flying around the craft. i lost sight both times of the craft because of jets showing up. 

after seeing the craft i became obsessed with this. i told people and they thought i was crazy, but i knew what i saw. i studied every ufo book photo i could find. i looked at ufo images on the net to see if i could find photos that resembled what i saw that night. so far no luck.

i can offer you no proof to what i saw. my only motivation is that maybe someone else has repoeted something simular at the same time. i don't remember the exact dates only taht it was near the mid to near the end of september 1999 in the city of thunder bay, ontario.

i am not a credible witness as i have two mental disorders. one being clinical depression and the other is attention deficeit disorder. i don't hallucinate visually or audibly. i know i saw something and maybe someone else did too.

                              sincerly
                                  
                                 brian niemi
content.summary: A two night each several hours in length sighting

content.detailedDescription:
I saw something when i was about 12 or 13 (so would have been about 1975-6). 

i live in rugby in the midlands, uk.  there are radio masts close to the town, some of which are used by the m.O.D., and you could see them at night from my bedroom window, due to the red warning lights they had on them.  a number of these have been removed within the last few years, but there are still some left in that location.

when i couldn't sleep, i used to look out of the window at the mast lights, and one night, while doing just that, i noticed a white light moving across the sky.  i couldn't tell how far away it was from me or the masts, but it moved across, from right to left, at approximately the speed i would have expected of a light aircraft.  naturally, that is what i first assumed it to be, but the light suddenly shot upwards at an angle of about 60 - 70 degrees, and was moving so quickly out of sight that i would have missed it if i had blinked.

i am 100% positive that this was not a light- or passenger aircraft, as it's last movements would be impossible for an aircraft to accomplish.

unfortunately, my sister, who shared the bedroom with me, remained asleep during the event, so i have no witness to validate my sighting.  i am now 43 years old, and this memory has remained very clear in my mind since that evening, as it was a very exciting event for me.
content.summary: White light seen moving across sky in evening, not aircraft.

content.detailedDescription: I was traveling north on idaho hwy 20 just before total dark. i saw some lights to the nnw that seemed a little high for house lights on the horizon so i just began watching them. rolled down my window to assure they weren't reflections. they rose higher and higher. they never got any bigger, just remained about the size and color of house lights on the horizon. there were 5 or 6, flashing a little and in a straight line. definitely not horizon lights. they eventially went directly over me. i did not pull over and didn't have a moonroof or anything so couldn't see them over head. i stuck my head out the window once, just to see. they were there and getting dimmer. i really thought i was going to be abducted or come up with missing time or something. i did not pull over. was too frightened. was sure that i would hear something about the lights on the news or something but never did.
content.summary: 5-6 lights in sky, in a straight row, blinking and moved toward and over my car then disappeared.
